It’s me again = call me crazy = #scanditron in the making
After last years epic roadtrip ➡️ #iberitron ⬅️
This year we go even further:
* 10.000 vs 8.000 Km (6.200 vs 5.000 miles)
* 11 vs 8 countries
* still one = my beloved e-tron S 
.
Route: Austria 🇦🇹 - Chech Republic 🇨🇿 - Germany 🇩🇪 - Danmark 🇩🇰 - Sweden 🇸🇪 - Norway 🇳🇴 - Finland 🇫🇮 - Estonia 🇪🇪 - Latvia 🇱🇻 - Lithuania 🇱🇹 - Poland 🇵🇱
.
Excited and curious what awaits us.
But charging ⚡️ is not something I am worrying about.
More the distances and timing them with all the farry 🚢 crossings and slow roads.
As always, I take you along via IG stories.
Stay tuned 😀

#iberitron log Book entry 01 or charging 🌅 romantic
Want to see our day by day progress
➡️ go to @audidriven stories section
.
I type this 1st log entry from Barcelona - ~ 2.000 Km into our 8.000 #iberitron road trip
.
Short summary how things went down till now:
* Austria is HPC heaven - except in Villach (see the drama in @audidriven story iberitron 02)
* Italy is getting better - although after our 3rd visit to @ionity.official Portogruaro - this location is definitely a dump (stinking trash containers next to the chargers, littering, not appealing at all
* @ionity.official France has a serious problem (1st station 4 stalls: 1 of 4 working = 1 broken - where I parked 1st, 2nd working - where I reparked, 3&4 only charging with ~35kW / 2nd station 6 stalls: 2 out of six delivered the full speed (150kW for the e-tron), the other ~35kW. Again lucky as I got the 2nd working one after reparking) Got lucky
* Spain 🇪🇸 - a little to early to tell but was already pleasantly surprised, as proven by this picture. In the middle of nowhere - Figueres - I found this working (!) HPC charger. Biggest challenge was to get the operator app working as it does not accept any of the charging cards
* A general not surprising rule: try to always charge before the night (like in this case) or even better over night as currently in our Barcelona hotel. For me the charging stops are part of the adventure (now locations, new experiences) but apparently my family thinks differently 😂. Yesterday we had zero charging stops (“boring” for me, enjoyable for family)
.
When we arrive at my moms place near Malaga I will try to do a more detailed day by day posts if desired 😉
.

Vienna - Munich - Vienna trip (to forget)
Charging was the least = none of our problems
.
Red Bull Salzburg got shot out of the stadium = 7:1 for Bayern Munich
Now I am finally COVID ✅
.
Nevertheless- the trip with our Avus silver ⚡️ bullet was again a pleasure
Up to 210 Km/h in Germany
Only 1 longer (because of us & hunger) charging stop on the return leg
Also due to - and that’s how it always should be - the overnight charging possibility to 100% at our Hotel
Thx @hiltonmunichpark - you obviously understand what the next differentiator in the hospitality industry will be 👍
.
